				\begin{document}$$ {\text{N}}_{2} + {\text{H}}_{2} \mathop{\longrightarrow}\limits^{{{{\text{BASF}} \text{-} {\text{S6}}0 \text{-} 10}}}{\text{NH}}_{3} $$\end{document}

Nanocatalysts are heralded as new process candidates exhibiting higher activity, greater stability, durability or recycling potential, efficient recovery characteristics, and cost effectiveness. These new catalysts are candidates for clean energy applications such as hydrogen generation, hydrogen storage and fuel cell applications. One promising use is for the synthesis of hydrogen peroxide.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
